text: White admiral may refer to: ==Butterflies== These butterfly species are commonly called white admirals: *In America it refers to two of the three (North American) subspecies of Limenitis arthemis *In Europe and Asia it refers to the (Eurasian) white admiral: Limenitis camilla *In India it refers to the Indian white admiral: Limenitis trivena ==Historical== *For the historical naval officer rank, see Admiral of the White.
